00:28:12.870 --> 00:28:14.170
But thank you for that question.

00:28:14.170 --> 00:28:15.470
Wow. I'm going to think about that.

00:28:15.470 --> 00:28:16.770
&gt;&gt; I Tweeted at you today.

00:28:16.770 --> 00:28:19.610
Hit me back and let's get
you to T C. Read aloud.

00:28:19.610 --> 00:28:20.910
Thanks.

00:28:20.910 --> 00:28:22.210
&gt;&gt; Hello.

00:28:22.210 --> 00:28:23.510
&gt;&gt; Kwame Alexander: Hello.

00:28:23.510 --> 00:28:24.810
&gt;&gt; Alright, so.

00:28:24.810 --> 00:28:27.740
I'm going to right off the
bat, I have never heard

00:28:27.740 --> 00:28:29.940
of these books before in my life.

00:28:29.940 --> 00:28:32.750
And as soon as I heard
the description I'm like,

00:28:32.750 --> 00:28:36.410
oh my God I need to buy these books
and put them in my school's library

00:28:36.410 --> 00:28:40.120
because there are some kids at
my school who need to read it.

00:28:40.120 --> 00:28:41.540
Who need to get this.

00:28:41.540 --> 00:28:46.050
Because I'm a very avid writer,
reader, artist, musician,

00:28:46.050 --> 00:28:48.650
poet, and I go to school.

00:28:48.650 --> 00:28:53.250
And there are five year olds, there
are seven year olds, who are stuck,

00:28:53.250 --> 00:28:56.450
who I see on their
iPhones texting away,

00:28:56.450 --> 00:28:59.430
saying they haven't read
a book in their lives.

00:28:59.430 --> 00:29:01.480
There are seven year
olds in my school,

00:29:01.480 --> 00:29:06.010
it's a private school,
but who can't read.

00:29:06.010 --> 00:29:09.660
And as, I've been reading since
I was three and a half years old,

00:29:09.660 --> 00:29:13.740
I've read the Harry Potter series
when I was like nine, I love books.

00:29:13.740 --> 00:29:16.930
I like reading them,
writing them, and the thought

00:29:16.930 --> 00:29:23.250 position:56%
that there are people out there who
are unable to connect to the stories

00:29:23.250 --> 00:29:26.490
on the page, it's horrifying.

00:29:26.490 --> 00:29:29.190
And

00:29:29.190 --> 00:29:30.490
&gt;&gt; Kwame Alexander: You're right.

00:29:30.490 --> 00:29:32.130
And I applaud you.

00:29:32.130 --> 00:29:34.400
What grade are you in?

00:29:34.400 --> 00:29:35.700
&gt;&gt; Eighth.

00:29:35.700 --> 00:29:37.000
&gt;&gt; Kwame Alexander:
You're in eighth grade?

00:29:37.000 --> 00:29:38.300
&gt;&gt; I think.

00:29:38.300 --> 00:29:39.600
&gt;&gt; Kwame Alexander: Wow,
that's really impressive.

00:29:39.600 --> 00:29:40.900
I applaud you, and I think
we've got to do more of this.

00:29:40.900 --> 00:29:43.030
We've got to have, that's why the
book festival is so important.

00:29:43.030 --> 00:29:45.010
Because it takes the
words off the page,

00:29:45.010 --> 00:29:46.920
it puts the words on the stage.

00:29:46.920 --> 00:29:49.050
It gives parents and
children an opportunity

00:29:49.050 --> 00:29:50.590
to connect around literature.

00:29:50.590 --> 00:29:52.510
So thank you so much for that.

00:29:52.510 --> 00:29:57.810
