00:29:57.810 --> 00:29:59.500
&gt;&gt; I'm from Beville Middle School

00:29:59.500 --> 00:30:01.610
and I was wondering
what would you say

00:30:01.610 --> 00:30:06.150
to future authors to
inspire them more?

00:30:06.150 --> 00:30:07.450
&gt;&gt; Kwame Alexander: So
we'll end with that.

00:30:07.450 --> 00:30:08.750
That's a very good point.

00:30:08.750 --> 00:30:12.930
What would I say to future
authors to inspire them?

00:30:12.930 --> 00:30:14.400
I would say it took me five years

00:30:14.400 --> 00:30:18.260
to get my novel, The
Crossover published.

00:30:18.260 --> 00:30:19.860
It took me 22 rejections.

00:30:19.860 --> 00:30:25.350
It took a lot of persistence
and a lot of will.

00:30:25.350 --> 00:30:30.900
And I think I would encourage
you to believe in yourself.

00:30:30.900 --> 00:30:36.090
To believe in your capacity
to create a story or a poem

00:30:36.090 --> 00:30:39.970
or something that's meaningful
and significant to other people.

00:30:39.970 --> 00:30:48.160
I would also encourage the
adults in the room to remember

00:30:48.160 --> 00:30:55.600
that adults don't sort of create
their prejudices and their ideas

00:30:55.600 --> 00:30:58.640
about the world out of a vacuum.

00:30:58.640 --> 00:31:02.470
The mind of an adult begins
in the imagination of a child.

00:31:02.470 --> 00:31:05.170
And we have to begin to create
literature and expose children

00:31:05.170 --> 00:31:08.270
to literature that's going to
make them into the kinds of people

00:31:08.270 --> 00:31:11.210
that we're going to be proud of
and that are going to represent

00:31:11.210 --> 00:31:15.980
and really create the kind of place
we really need and want in America.

00:31:15.980 --> 00:31:18.510
So thank you all so much
and have a great day.

